PN,39902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1780942271
OL,3,CAssociate of Manchester Synagogue
OL,4,Cattacker admits to terror charges
OL,6,FThe charge say he drove Jihad Al-
OL,7,FShamie - with the intention of
OL,8,Fcommitting an act of terrorism or
OL,9,Fassisting AlShamie to do so - to the
OL,10,FUK Defence Academy in Shrivenham,
OL,11,FOxfordshire, on 14 August 2025 to
OL,12,Fcarry out hostile reconnaissance of
OL,13,Fthe location.
OL,15,FThe trip came weeks before Al-Shamie
OL,16,Flaunched his attack on the Heaton Park
OL,17,FHebrew Synagogue in Crumpsall, on 2
OL,18,FOctober.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1780942271
OL,3,CAssociate of Manchester Synagogue
OL,4,Cattacker admits to terror charges
OL,6,FWorshippers Melvin Cravitz, 66, died
OL,7,Falong with Adrian Daulby, 53, were
OL,8,Fkilled after 35-year-old Al-Shamie, a
OL,9,FSyrian-born UK citizen, drove his Kia
OL,10,FPicanto into the gates of the
OL,11,Fsynagogue and began attacking with a
OL,12,Fknife, wearing a fake suicide belt.
OL,14,FHe was shot dead by armed police as he
OL,15,Fcarried out the attack.
OL,17,FBashir was arrested at Manchester
OL,18,FAirport on 27 November but was not
OL,19,Fcharged in relation to the synagogue
OL,20,Fattack.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1780942271
OL,3,CAssociate of Manchester Synagogue
OL,4,Cattacker admits to terror charges
OL,6,FThe defendant had previously denied
OL,7,Fpreparation of terrorist acts by
OL,8,Fassisting AlShamie and had also
OL,9,Fpleaded not guilty to three counts of
OL,10,Fdisseminating terrorist publications
OL,11,Frelating to Jihad and martyrdom on a
OL,12,FWhatsApp chat group on dates in
OL,13,FNovember and December 2024.
OL,15,FProsecutor Jonathan Polnay KC told the
OL,16,Fcourt these charges were part of the
OL,17,Fbackground to the more serious charge,
OL,18,Fwhich Bashir had admitted.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1780942271
OL,3,CAssociate of Manchester Synagogue
OL,4,Cattacker admits to terror charges
OL,6,FHe said that in these circumstances,
OL,7,Fthe court could pass a sentence on
OL,8,FBashir that "reflects the seriousness
OL,9,Fof the offending behaviour".
OL,11,FHe invited the court to order the
OL,12,Foutstanding charges to lie on file.
OL,14,FMr Polnay said he had received a basis
OL,15,Fof plea from the defence which would
OL,16,Fbe considered by the prosecution.
OL,18,FMrs Justice Cheema-Grubb set a two-day
OL,19,Fsentencing hearing at Manchester Crown
OL,20,FCourt on 20 and 21 July.
OL,26,@pD@MOUqD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
